Description: Slim AndroidAuto UI for Raspberry Pi
 Crankshaft Slim UI provides a lightweight AndroidAuto projection interface
 designed for embedded automotive infotainment systems running on Raspberry Pi.
 .
 Features:
  * AndroidAuto projection (USB and wireless)
  * Minimal settings interface (brightness, volume, connection preferences)
  * Responsive QML-based interface (800x480 to 1920x1080)
  * Multiple display backend support (EGLFS, VNC)
  * Graceful audio backend degradation (PulseAudio/ALSA)
  * Touch input forwarding to AndroidAuto
  * Error handling with user-friendly dialogs
  * Memory efficient (<150MB during active projection)
 .
 This package includes:
  * crankshaft-slim-ui executable
  * systemd service unit
  * QML UI components
  * Configuration files
  * Documentation
